Sentencas: The phase relations and crystal structures of La1-xSrxFe1-yTayO3 in the compositional range x = 0-0.60, y = 0-0.20 were investigated by powder X-ray diffraction (XRD).
Titulo: Characterization of tantalum doped lanthanum strontium ferrite as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The formal concentration of Fe4+ in the La1-xSrxFe1-yTayO3 +/- w (LSFT) system was calculated and related to the electrical/electrochemical properties.
Titulo: Characterization of tantalum doped lanthanum strontium ferrite as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: To investigate the electrochemical behaviour as cathode material for SOFCs, impedance measurements were performed on LSFT/electrolyte/LSFT symmetrical cells by using La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3, (LSGM) as electrolyte material.
Titulo: Characterization of tantalum doped lanthanum strontium ferrite as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The lowest area specific resistance (ASR), derived from the polarization resistance (R-p), 1 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C, was measured for the LSFT compound doped with x = 0.40 and y = 0.05.
Titulo: Characterization of tantalum doped lanthanum strontium ferrite as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells
